1
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:49,399
I didn't go looking for you,

2
00:00:49,719 --> 00:00:51,399
yet you showed up at my door yourself.

3
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:55,600
Tell me.

4
00:00:55,880 --> 00:00:56,920
What exactly do you know?

5
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:58,799
That fire wasn't an accident,

6
00:00:58,880 --> 00:00:59,479
was it?

7
00:00:59,640 --> 00:01:00,719
It's been ten years, hasn't it?

8
00:01:01,679 --> 00:01:03,520
And only now you decide to seek the truth.

9
00:01:04,879 --> 00:01:05,920
Some truths,

10
00:01:06,239 --> 00:01:07,680
even if burned to ashes,

11
00:01:08,359 --> 00:01:10,680
are cleaner than the bloody remnants.

12
00:01:11,079 --> 00:01:12,000
What do you mean?

13
00:01:13,799 --> 00:01:14,920
What exactly do you know?

14
00:01:15,120 --> 00:01:15,959
In three days,

15
00:01:16,439 --> 00:01:17,599
bring your cue.

16
00:01:18,280 --> 00:01:19,159
Win a game,

17
00:01:20,359 --> 00:01:21,519
get an answer.

18
00:01:28,159 --> 00:01:29,000
Fine.

19
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:32,599
Even if I have to bet my life,

20
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:35,840
I'll play to the end.

21
00:01:40,640 --> 00:01:41,560
I like that.

22
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:44,920
Some gamblers

23
00:01:45,280 --> 00:01:47,120
always think they can turn the tables.

24
00:02:42,439 --> 00:02:43,080
Bet it all.

25
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:48,719
He's here.

26
00:03:02,080 --> 00:03:03,439
Finally here.

27
00:03:26,240 --> 00:03:27,680
Distinguished guests,

28
00:03:28,199 --> 00:03:29,560
good evening.

29
00:03:29,879 --> 00:03:30,840
Welcome to

30
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:32,919
this billiards-themed luxury yacht.

31
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:34,360
For the next three days and two nights,

32
00:03:35,080 --> 00:03:35,800
everyone

33
00:03:36,159 --> 00:03:38,280
will enjoy a wonderful time.

34
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:40,520
Oh, by the way,

35
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:42,240
for tonight's billiards match,

36
00:03:42,719 --> 00:03:44,759
we have specially invited the

37
00:03:44,759 --> 00:03:46,000
genius billiards player from ten years ago,

38
00:03:46,439 --> 00:03:47,240
the Triple Crown Champion,

39
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:48,520
Cheng Ye.

40
00:03:49,199 --> 00:03:50,159
That's Cheng Ye?

41
00:03:50,439 --> 00:03:51,120
Yeah.

42
00:03:51,280 --> 00:03:52,520
Wasn't he banned from competing?

43
00:03:53,319 --> 00:03:54,280
Why is Cheng Ye here?

44
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:55,159
Why is he here?

45
00:03:57,199 --> 00:03:57,680
Let's go take a look.

46
00:03:57,680 --> 00:03:58,599
He's really amazing.

47
00:04:07,599 --> 00:04:08,240
By the way,

48
00:04:08,639 --> 00:04:10,639
our Triple Crown Champion, Cheng Ye,

49
00:04:12,039 --> 00:04:13,719
has another identity now.

50
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:15,400
That is...

51
00:04:17,639 --> 00:04:18,480
a delivery man,

52
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:19,759
Black Eight.

53
00:04:21,639 --> 00:04:22,959
It really is the Triple Crown Champion, Cheng Ye.

54
00:04:23,120 --> 00:04:23,759
He's making a comeback.

55
00:04:24,279 --> 00:04:25,160
No way.

56
00:04:25,319 --> 00:04:26,519
Did he fail at delivering takeout

57
00:04:26,519 --> 00:04:27,680
and come back to play pool?

58
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:31,079
The pool world isn't easy to survive in now.

59
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:32,519
It's been ten years. Is he still any good?

60
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:33,920
Who knows?

61
00:04:34,079 --> 00:04:34,879
Maybe.

62
00:04:45,519 --> 00:04:46,399
Bosses,

63
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:47,920
the betting is open.

64
00:04:48,199 --> 00:04:50,240
I'll kick things off for you bosses.

65
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:53,480
Ten million.

66
00:04:53,879 --> 00:04:55,040
I bet Black Eight loses.

67
00:05:00,399 --> 00:05:01,319
Feel free to place your bets.

68
00:05:01,439 --> 00:05:02,000
Good.

69
00:05:02,519 --> 00:05:03,439
I'll match that.

70
00:05:11,319 --> 00:05:12,720
Let's play something interesting.

71
00:05:13,319 --> 00:05:14,600
Whoever rolls the lowest number

72
00:05:14,759 --> 00:05:15,399
breaks first.

73
00:05:15,879 --> 00:05:17,519
Pool relies on skill,

74
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:19,120
not luck.

75
00:05:21,439 --> 00:05:22,319
Well said.

76
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,680
Too bad, though.

77
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:26,920
The rules here

78
00:05:27,399 --> 00:05:28,759
are up to me.

79
00:05:48,160 --> 00:05:49,480
Guess what I rolled.

80
00:05:51,759 --> 00:05:53,240
There are six dice in total.

81
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:55,439
The lowest possible roll should be six, right?

82
00:05:56,199 --> 00:05:57,839
Jiu Ge never misses.

83
00:05:58,079 --> 00:05:59,560
Then Jiu Ge definitely wins.

84
00:06:00,480 --> 00:06:01,399
One.

85
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:04,319
Amazing!

86
00:06:04,399 --> 00:06:05,279
As expected of Jiu Ge.

87
00:06:05,399 --> 00:06:06,399
What's the point of competing?

88
00:06:06,920 --> 00:06:08,120
With Jiu Ge taking the break,

89
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:09,360
he can finish him off instantly.

90
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:27,800
Still struggling in vain?

91
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:29,480
No matter how you shake it,

92
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:31,040
you can't shake out The Pillar Stack.

93
00:06:32,079 --> 00:06:32,839
In such a hurry?

94
00:06:33,839 --> 00:06:34,879
You didn't even look at the dice

95
00:06:34,879 --> 00:06:35,879
before getting ready to break.

96
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:39,519
It's not that I look down on you,

97
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,600
but you can't even roll a six,

98
00:06:41,879 --> 00:06:43,480
let alone The Pillar Stack.

99
00:06:49,680 --> 00:06:50,879
That's way too impressive!

100
00:06:52,639 --> 00:06:53,839
He actually shattered them!

101
00:06:53,839 --> 00:06:55,360
That strength is insane!

102
00:06:55,439 --> 00:06:56,720
He can even shatter dice!

103
00:06:57,879 --> 00:06:58,439
The dice are broken.

104
00:06:58,759 --> 00:06:59,480
This round doesn't count.

105
00:06:59,639 --> 00:07:01,319
You only said whoever has the lower points wins.

106
00:07:01,720 --> 00:07:03,160
You didn't say we couldn't break the dice.

107
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:05,519
Everyone here can testify for me.

108
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:09,839
So, you have one point.

109
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:11,920
I have zero points.

110
00:07:16,639 --> 00:07:17,240
You lose.

111
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:19,079
I break.

112
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:38,800
Beautiful!

113
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:40,160
Two stripes down right off the break.

114
00:07:40,160 --> 00:07:40,639
Two stripes down right off the break.

115
00:07:40,839 --> 00:07:41,600
Without a doubt,

116
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:42,920
he'll definitely choose stripes.

117
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:46,519
The layout is complicated now.

118
00:07:46,639 --> 00:07:48,680
The other four stripes are frozen to the cushion,

119
00:07:49,040 --> 00:07:51,560
and they're in a death grip with four solids.

120
00:07:52,079 --> 00:07:53,639
This game is really high difficulty.

121
00:08:05,079 --> 00:08:06,240
He has to play defense on this shot.

122
00:08:06,240 --> 00:08:07,040
There's no shot to make.

123
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:18,040
Truly worthy of being the Triple Crown Champion.

124
00:08:21,879 --> 00:08:23,519
That was truly a stroke of genius.

125
00:08:23,839 --> 00:08:24,639
This ten ball...

126
00:08:24,759 --> 00:08:26,000
after two caroms,

127
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:27,720
he cut it right in!

128
00:08:29,399 --> 00:08:30,360
All in! All in! All in!

129
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:31,519
Raise the stakes!

130
00:08:32,519 --> 00:08:33,159
Raise the stakes!

131
00:08:34,039 --> 00:08:34,759
This shot...

132
00:08:35,159 --> 00:08:36,879
I think he's going to clear the table.

133
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:37,799
This kid...

134
00:08:37,919 --> 00:08:38,600
has skills.

135
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:40,320
Worthy of being the Ball King.

136
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:48,720
Exactly.

137
00:08:49,519 --> 00:08:50,519
An extreme bank shot!

138
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:51,840
He's got god-like vision!

139
00:08:51,919 --> 00:08:53,080
A champion is a champion.

140
00:08:53,399 --> 00:08:54,440
Ten years have passed,

141
00:08:54,559 --> 00:08:55,759
and his skills are still top-notch.

142
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:56,519
Yeah.

143
00:08:56,799 --> 00:08:57,679
This problem-solving strategy

144
00:08:57,679 --> 00:08:58,759
is enough for us to study for a year.

145
00:08:58,879 --> 00:08:59,919
Is he really going to clear the table?

146
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:00,679
You're bluffing.

147
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:02,240
Didn't you see the position of the 8-ball?

148
00:09:02,559 --> 00:09:04,120
If this shot knocks the 8-ball in,

149
00:09:04,399 --> 00:09:05,559
Black Eight loses.

150
00:09:06,159 --> 00:09:08,240
When I bet on Black Eight earlier,

151
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:10,240
why didn't I notice the 8-ball's position?

152
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:11,240
Bet too early, huh?

153
00:09:11,320 --> 00:09:13,080
I saw the 8-ball's position long ago.

154
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:15,320
This is a dead end.

155
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:16,200
No one can solve this.

156
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:22,320
How does it feel to dig your own grave?

157
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:25,159
The 8-ball is blocked so tightly.

158
00:09:25,639 --> 00:09:26,600
Even if it goes in,

159
00:09:28,159 --> 00:09:29,679
at best it's a draw.

160
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:31,279
After all that effort,

161
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:33,360
do you really think you are Black Eight?

162
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:36,480
Just

163
00:09:48,159 --> 00:09:49,519
playing tricks.

164
00:10:08,759 --> 00:10:09,600
That actually worked?!

165
00:10:10,879 --> 00:10:11,600
Magic!

166
00:10:13,440 --> 00:10:14,480
What magic?

167
00:10:14,879 --> 00:10:15,639
Physics.

168
00:10:16,120 --> 00:10:17,480
Bernoulli's principle.

169
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:18,840
What principle?

170
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:26,399
Celestial Six Styles: Wind Blade.

171
00:10:29,639 --> 00:10:30,360
Wow.

172
00:10:30,919 --> 00:10:31,600
Magic.

173
00:10:32,159 --> 00:10:32,879
Physics.

174
00:10:33,759 --> 00:10:36,360
The cue ball's spin generates a wind blade,

175
00:10:36,919 --> 00:10:39,080
which, without touching the ball,

176
00:10:39,519 --> 00:10:42,080
can move the target ball's position.

177
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:48,759
Brilliant!

178
00:10:48,879 --> 00:10:49,679
Brilliant!

179
00:10:50,039 --> 00:10:51,320
Truly brilliant!

180
00:10:51,399 --> 00:10:52,399
Two balls in one shot!

181
00:10:53,159 --> 00:10:54,120
Thank you, Boss Jiang.

182
00:10:54,679 --> 00:10:55,879
Sorry for making you spend so much.

183
00:10:57,879 --> 00:10:59,279
This was truly

184
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:00,639
a good match.

185
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:19,440
Is this also physics?

186
00:11:19,919 --> 00:11:20,559
What law is it?

187
00:11:20,919 --> 00:11:21,279
This...

188
00:11:21,279 --> 00:11:22,159
I don't understand either.

189
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:31,080
I thought there'd be a more novel playing style.

190
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:32,159
It was the last ball.

191
00:11:32,159 --> 00:11:33,000
He just had to show off.

192
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:34,679
Aren't you afraid of pushing your luck?

193
00:11:34,960 --> 00:11:36,639
Luckily, the last ball went in.

194
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:39,200
What are you showing off for?

195
00:11:40,159 --> 00:11:41,279
Now you can tell me...

196
00:11:41,279 --> 00:11:42,200
...the truth about Wei Wei.

197
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:44,200
You want to know the truth after winning just one game?

198
00:11:44,799 --> 00:11:45,799
Do you know the rules?

199
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:48,200
Best of three.

200
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:49,840
But next...

201
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:52,320
You won't win again.

202
00:12:00,080 --> 00:12:02,200
Is this the surprise you prepared specially for me?

203
00:12:02,759 --> 00:12:03,200
Boss Nan.

204
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:04,399
Boss Nan.

205
00:12:07,440 --> 00:12:08,080
Quiet.

206
00:12:11,639 --> 00:12:13,360
Eyes, one hundred thousand.

207
00:12:14,039 --> 00:12:14,840
Liver...

208
00:12:15,279 --> 00:12:15,759
Fifty.

209
00:12:16,320 --> 00:12:17,279
Lungs, seventy.

210
00:12:17,279 --> 00:12:18,799
Heart, one million.

211
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:23,039
Ten million US dollars.

212
00:12:23,559 --> 00:12:25,559
To pay this off with your life...

213
00:12:26,559 --> 00:12:28,120
It would take thirty lifetimes.

214
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:30,559
What will you pay with?

215
00:12:31,759 --> 00:12:32,240
Boss Nan.

216
00:12:32,399 --> 00:12:32,919
Boss Nan.

217
00:12:34,159 --> 00:12:34,679
I...

218
00:12:56,120 --> 00:12:56,759
Hello?

219
00:12:56,759 --> 00:12:57,759
Brilliant.

220
00:12:57,759 --> 00:12:58,720
Truly brilliant.

221
00:12:58,759 --> 00:12:59,440
Boss Jiang.

222
00:13:00,039 --> 00:13:01,960
I want to add another ten million dollars on the next match.

223
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:03,960
I've already had someone send the chips over.

224
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:06,080
The Triple Crown Champion is indeed the Triple Crown Champion.

225
00:13:06,399 --> 00:13:08,000
I didn't expect that after ten years without playing...

226
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:09,080
...he's still so formidable.

227
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:10,120
It's really surprising.

228
00:13:11,279 --> 00:13:12,240
Alright, Boss Sun.

229
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:13,759
Have a pleasant trip.

230
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:20,519
Come.

231
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:22,639
Business is here.

232
00:13:23,399 --> 00:13:25,480
This is a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity.

233
00:13:27,120 --> 00:13:28,200
Make sure you seize it.

234
00:13:28,559 --> 00:13:30,159
U-Understood, Boss Nan.

235
00:13:30,320 --> 00:13:30,799
This time...

236
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:32,679
I absolutely won't let any accidents happen.

237
00:13:34,200 --> 00:13:35,879
If you dare let him win again...

238
00:13:36,399 --> 00:13:39,440
I will make you disappear from this world completely.
